         <abstract>
            <p>We consider the problem of estimating numerically the parameters of singularities of solutions of differential equations. We propose a novel approach which is based on discretizing the governing equation and "time-stepping" in the complex domain. Some applications to ordinary and partial differential equations are discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
